    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA222-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi talaimakaṉ varavuṇarntu ciṟaippuṟamākac ceṟippaṟivuṟīi varaivu kaṭāyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante urged for marriage by informing [him] about [HER] confinement when she had understood HIS coming [and] he was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA222">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            karuṅkāl vēṅkaic cevvī vāṅkuciṉai</l>
<l>            vaṭukkoḷap piṇitta viṭumuri muraṟcik</l>
<l>            kaipuṉai ciṟuneṟi vāṅkip paiyeṉa</l>
<l>            vicumpā ṭāymayil kaṭuppa yāṉiṉṟu</l>
<l>            pacuṅkā ḻalkul paṟṟuvaṉa ṉūkkic </l>
<l>            celavuṭaṉ viṭukō tōḻi palavuṭaṉ</l>
<l>            vāḻai yōṅkiya vaḻaiyamai cilampiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟuñcupiṭi maruṅkiṉ mañcupaṭak kāṇātu</l>
<l>            peruṅkaḷiṟu piḷiṟuñ cōlaiyavar</l>
<l>            cēṇeṭuṅ kuṉṟaṅ kāṇiya nīyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Shall I let go of [you] altogether, friend, into movement,</l>
<l rend="indent2">swinging [you] as I grasp<note place="foot">Here <term xml:lang="ta">paṟṟuvaṉaṉ</term>, p.a. of the 1st sg., has to be taken as a <term xml:lang="ta">muṟṟeccam</term>.</note> [your] hip with the green girdle</l>
<l rend="indent">today<note place="foot">Syntax and message are in no way clear, and the marking seems completely arbitrary. T.V.G. interprets this as an invitation of the confidante to HER to set her moving in the swing. This device might or might not be described in lines 1-3, in any case it is not clearly named.</note>, [for you] to resemble a peacock dancing in the sky,</l>
<l rend="indent2">gently, bending the small [swing-]curve<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">neṟi</term>, the frequent word for the path, is taken here by T.V.G. to mean swing.</note> fashioned by hand,</l>
<l rend="indent">on the cord with way-giving bends(?) fettered so that it is injured</l>
<l rend="indent">to the red-blossomed bending branch of the black-trunked Vēṅkai?</l>
<l rend="indent">– for you to see his distant long hill</l>
<l rend="indent3">with groves, where the big elephant bull trumpets,</l>
<l rend="indent">not seeing, since clouds come up, the sleeping female by [his] side</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the mountain side joined by Vaḻai trees where the plantains</l>
<l rend="indent4">have become high, many together.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
